    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Former farmland known as the Seminole Improvement District became Westlake in 2014 when Minto Communities bought 3,800 acres for $51 million.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Westlake%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Westlake officially joined Palm Beach County as its 39th municipality on June 22 2016 after a special election.",
